items.name: BestBoyNido
items.description:
Introducing the best boy in the world!

Nido!

I immortalized one of my dogs' likeness with this LoRA! Nido is an absolute gentleman. When his sister snaps at him, he lets her win even though he's bigger. When the old girl growls at him, he lets out a big apology wiggle. He waits until the bed is made before asking permission to get up. He's just the best boy in the whole wide world, and now everyone can take him on the adventures he deserves. At just 19MB, this thing packs a punch! I put together this LoRA workflow with 6-prompts per queue to help with sampling new LoRA's. If you're using the base SDXL you'll want to add the SDXL refiner into the flow. DreamShaper XL and other checkpoints with their own built in refiners don't need it. No upscale involved because it tends to triple the generation time. Default batch is 2 per prompt. Default resolution is 1344Wx768H.

Questions? You can find me on my Discord server at The Terrace

The Candy Mix is a clone of the Anything_v3 and it includes a cooking recipe.

Cooking recipe

Candy Mix recipe

VAE

  • kl-f8-anime2.ckpt is baked in.

Recommends

  • All posted images use "DDetailer script extension" or "After Detailer" for beautiful faces.

  • "EasyNegative" "negative_hand-neg", "ng_deepnegative_v1_75t" embeddings are recommended in the negative prompt.

  • SuperMerger extension

  • Lora Block Weight extension

  • webui model toolkit to examine LoRAs and models.

items.name: Clay style
items.description:
这是做粘土风格的lora，训练图用了81张训练图,

底模用的是revAnimated_v122，尺寸是512x768,描述词简单描述就好了，

例如1 男孩, 草地, 户外, 天空, 短发, 单人, 天, 花朵, 云, 草, 叶, 微笑, 杰作, 最佳质量, Chibi 简单背景...

我试了迪士尼，dreamshaper，chilloutmix_Nim那些偏3D的大模型模型也合适，权重调看着调就好；

在图生图，我把之前生成是图拖进来，加上这个lora（适当调下权重），再加上controlnet，之前的图就会加上粘土材质；粘土风格这个比较小众，个人感觉这个lora有点点点点点鸡肋 ╮(๑•́ ₃•̀๑)╭

The following is machine translated

items.name: sfy | a character lora trained by only one picture
items.description:
2023.8.3 update:

  • I use kohya_ss's svd_merge_lora.py to change the lora's dimension from 128 to 32 and make it become much smaller. In some cases, the character can't keep same with the original picture, but most time it still works well.

Original:

  • This is a character lora that trained by only one picture on SDXL1.0(a full body picture generated by a merged checkpoint which is SD1.5 version, then cut it into an upper body picture and a head picture, I think it can be called "trained by only one picture").

  • It's a test to find out if we can get a character lora who don't have many pictures or even just generated by AI and you want to keep him/her.

  • You can change the character's action and clothes by prompts. In SD1.5, it's much easier because there're many high quality checkpoints in the same style, and you can also use Clothing lora and controlnet to change it (I have already tried it and it work well). But maybe SDXL will do it better in the future.

  • Now this lora is not pretty well, the clothes can't be replaced completely, but maybe I'll push other version which can solve this problem in the future. (You can follow the lora's metadata to train another one in SD1.5, it must be better.)

  • I recommend using DPM++ SDE Karras with weight 1.0.

items.name: Yummy - Food Photography Studio
items.description:
"Yummy" is a specialized LoRa (Low-Rank Adaptation) designed to assist you in generating captivating food photography. Whether you are a food blogger, a chef, a restaurant owner, or simply a food enthusiast, "Yummy" offers a diverse collection of high-quality food images to enhance your culinary projects.

Thoroughly tested and optimized, "Yummy" seamlessly adapts to various aspect ratios, making it easy to integrate the generated images into your websites, social media posts, menus, and marketing materials. From appetizing dishes to delightful desserts, "Yummy" provides a wide range of food visuals to suit your needs.

It is important to consider the initial resolution when using "Yummy" for generating images. Although the model can handle higher resolutions, we recommend applying the high-res fix to prevent any potential distortions. Starting with a maximum resolution of 768 along one side is advised for optimal results.

Your support is greatly appreciated and motivates meto continue refining "Yummy" and exploring new LoRAs in the future. If you find "Yummy" helpful for your projects, please consider supporting me through the provided PayPal link -> https://paypal.me/prezydent
